RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRECEDENT LUKE assumed command away from the start, was well rated through modest fractions along the backstretch run, confronted by WE CAN at the quarter marker, battled with that rival into the stretch, came again to take the lead at the furlong pole, drifted out into deep stretch, was kept to task into the final stages and held in a drive to prevail. LONG JACKET unhurried leaving the start, settled while saving ground into the backstretch run, maintained an inside path into the far turn, offered a sustained rally through the stretch, could not reel in the winner in the late stages and held safely for second. TWELVE VOLT forwardly placed in the early stages, took back into the backstretch run and tracked the moderate pace from the second flight, gained ground three wide at the quarter marker, raced four wide into the stretch then shifted in inside of the furlong marker, was gaining in deep stretch and was up in time to secure third. RIGHT HAND RYDER allowed to settle, tracked outside of rivals to the second turn, was roused four wide into the stretch, was gaining in the final furlong but needed more in the late stages and was outfinished for third. WE CAN close up to the moderate pace, tracked outside of PRECEDENT LUKE to the far turn, took a narrow lead at the quarter marker, battled with PRECEDENT LUKE into the lane, lacked a response in the late stages and weakened in deep stretch. TREE HUGGER a bit keen early, stalked the modest pace while saving ground to the second turn, tipped two wide for the drive, lost ground at the furlong pole and weakened. RANDY'SFURRYFRIEND took back off of the moderate pace, was asked for run three wide into the stretch and did not factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Precedent Luke
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace,well rated,battled stretch,drifted late,kept to task,driving

ENTRY.OWNER: Akin Zvika Avery Greg and Sherman Art

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 6F All Weather Track CR: 82. Starter Allowance Purse 16500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A ROUSING BABE unhurried away from the start, tracked outside of runners into the turn and was coaxed along three wide to the quarter marker, came in a bit tight into upper stretch and angled four wide for the drive, rallied at the furlong marker, responded to urging into deep stretch, surged in the final strides and won the nod on the wire to prevail. RAVEN'S QUEST close up in the opening stages, took back and tracked the solid pace into the turn, loomed three wide at the quarter marker and battled for the lead into the stretch, gained command and took a narrow advantage to the sixteenth-marker, dug in into deep stretch and was tagged for the win in the final strides. FIVE O COCKTAIL took back off of the solid early pace and tracked from the inside, came in tight approaching the turn and was shuffled back at the three-furlong marker, chased to the quarter pole then swung five wide for the drive, closed willingly while widest in deep stretch and was up in time to secure third. LAURA BRANIGAN prominent in the early running, stalked the solid pace into the turn then advanced to press the pace two wide at the quarter pole, battled for the lead into the stretch, fought back into the final sixteenth, came in a bit tight and steadied in deep stretch and could not muster a late response. PACIFIC ZIP rated off of the solid early pace, gained ground into the turn then came in tight while two wide nearing the top of the stretch, raced in traffic to the furlong grounds, found room into the late stages but lacked a late response. BLURSDAY sent to establish the early lead, showed good speed while dictating terms into the turn, pressed by LAURA BRANIGAN to the quarter marker, was overtaken into the stretch and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Blursday
ENTRY.COMMENT: good early speed inside,gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 88. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. RACE.FOOTNOTES: FRIED ASPARAGUS broke well and vied for the early lead outside of SHE'S SO SHINY, then floated a bit wide on the clubhouse turn and was content to stalk just off the flank of that rival to the far turn, took command passing the three furlong marker and won clear while under a drive to the line. SHE'S SO SHINY broke well and seized the lead and the rail, was allowed to set reasonable fractions while under a snug hold from the rider, tried to slip away with three furlongs to run but could not hold off the challenge of FRIED ASPARAGUS, kept on under steady handling and held well in the end for second. DOWNBURST was unhurried early tracking well behind the top pair, came under a drive from the three furlong pole, mounted a four wide rally into the stretch, closed well in the drive and missed for second, while holding clearly for third. TEN THE SMART WAY lunged at the start and was off slowly, rushed up into the first turn and stalked the decent pace from a two wide path into the backstretch, chased the leading pair into the far turn, raced three wide into stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker and tired in the final stages. SMOKEMS TAPHOUSE unhurried in the early stages, trailed to the far turn, rallied in the final furlong but failed to make an impact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M All Weather Track CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.

LAURA'S KIDOUGH settled four wide into the first turn, gained ground at the half-mile marker and improved position four wide at the quarter pole, came within aim in upper stretch and vied for the lead at the furlong marker, battled with VINNIEBOB into the final sixteenth, took a slim lead in deep stretch and was nailed on the line for the win, while just holding for the place at the finish. VINNIEBOB forwardly placed away from the start, tracked three wide along the first turn then tracked between runners into the backstretch, made a middle move and slipped to the rail nearing the far turn, was well placed while saving ground at the quarter marker, loomed nearing the top of the lane and took command inside of the three-sixteenths, dug in while leading into the final sixteenth, could not hold off the top pair in deep stretch and was gamely bested for the win and place, while well clear for the show. UPRIGHT away in good order and prominent to begin, took back to track the early pace and raced outside of rivals into the backstretch run, maintained an outside path while tracking to the half-mile pole, mounted a three wide bid at the quarter marker, lost ground at the furlong pole and flattened out in the late stages. LEVON asked for speed away from the start and assumed command into the first turn, pulled on the rider and opened to a clear lead into the backstretch run, set decent fractions to the half-mile marker and dictated terms into the far turn, came under pressure at the top of the stretch, battled to the furlong grounds, could not keep pace into the final sixteenth and weakened. THE SLAP forwardly placed in the early stages, tracked the decent pace from a three wide path along the first turn, raced between runners through the backstretch run and was coaxed along three wide and between runners into the far turn, came in tight and was boxed in at the quarter marker, found room into the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, was outrun into the final sixteenth and did not offer a late rally. L L L COOL forwardly placed away from the start, stalked the decent pace into the backstretch run, was well positioned at the half-mile marker and chased two wide into the far turn, lost ground into the stretch and gave way. UPDRAFT tracked the early pace from the second flight, was well positioned heading to the half-mile marker, could not keep pace into the second turn and did not threaten. STOUT fractious prior to the start, was unhurried and saved ground into the first turn, settled through the backstretch run and raced two wide into the far turn, was asked for run four wide into the drive and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 22500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DULY NOTED allowed to settle away from the start, tracked the decent pace between runners into the turn and raced three wide to the quarter marker, was roused four wide into the stretch and was full of run approaching the furlong grounds, vied for the lead inside of the furlong pole and battled with BROADWAY TIGER into the final sixteenth, repelled the runner-up in deep stretch and edged away in the end to prove best. BROADWAY TIGER broke sharply, conceded the early lead and tracked the solid pace into the turn, advanced two wide along the bend and pressed HOT AND SPICY to the quarter marker, took command into upper stretch and was set down for the drive, held foes at bay to mid-stretch then drifted out inside of the furlong marker, met the bid of DULY NOTED into the final sixteenth, was outfinished by the winner in deep stretch and was clear in the end for second. SHANA MADEL tracked the solid early pace three wide, was steered two wide into the turn and gained ground at the quarter marker, mounted a three wide bid into the stretch and continued her advance at the furlong marker, raced in tight quarters inside of the furlong marker, took up nearing the sixteenth-pole and was not able to match strides with the top pair in deep stretch, while clear of the rest for third. STAY UP allowed to settle away from the start, tracked outside of runners in the early stages then shifted to the rail along the turn, chased from the inside heading to the quarter marker then swung five wide for the drive, could not muster the needed response in deep stretch and passed tiring rivals late. LITTLE NAUGHTY close up in the early going, chased the solid pace between runners into the turn then slipped to the rail while in pursuit heading to the quarter pole, chased from the inside into the stretch, lost ground at the furlong marker and lacked a late response. VELOCIOUS crowded at the start and was away a step slowly, chased the solid early pace from the inside, became rank and hard to place and steadied approaching the turn, was steered two wide to the quarter marker and raced three wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker and tired in the final sixteenth. HOT AND SPICY hustled to assumed command in the early going, showed good speed while dictating terms into the turn, was pressed through solid fractions to the quarter marker, was overtaken in upper stretch, battled to the furlong marker and faded in the late stages. DIVINE GIFT chased outside of runners in the early stages, improved position four wide approaching the quarter marker, maintained that four wide path into the stretch, was outrun to the furlong marker and did not threaten in the final stages. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE RUNNING IN DEEP STRETCH. THE STEWARDS RULED THAT BROADWAY TIGER DRIFTED INTO THE PATH OF SHANA MADEL INSIDE OF THE FURLONG POLE AND CAUSED SHANA MADEL TO TAKE UP IN DEEP STRETCH. THIS ACTION COST SHANA MADEL THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING AND BROADWAY TIGER WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM SECOND AND PLACED THIRD.

OUR BOLD PRINCE was keen from the outset and pressed the early pace three deep while under a stout hold, was let loose after passing the three furlong marker, took the lead briefly in the stretch, ran on gamely to the wire but was outfinished by the winner. GROWTH ENGINE broke sharply and set a pressured pace to the turn, hung in to the stretch then gave way approaching the eighth pole. RACE.FOOTNOTES: HARMON was allowed to settle into stride near the back of the pack, stayed outside in the clear down the backstretch, circled the field on the far turn, came seven wide into the stretch and ran on well under steady handling to get up in time. BUENISIMO unhurried while racing three wide through the clubhouse turn, settled mid-pack down the backstretch, launched a bid from just before the five-sixteenths pole, swung five wide into the stretch and produced a steady rally to gain second. LOOKIN FOR REVENGE was a little slow to get into stride but recovered quickly and raced just behind the leading pair through the early stages while saving ground, responded to strong handling from the five-sixteenths marker, kept to task and gained the third spot.
